Kamarudeen Ogundele, Abuja The Presidential Panel on Citizens Data Management and harmonisation has been given March 16 deadline to submit its report. This is as the committee began its assignment on Tuesday. It was learnt that the Minister of Interior, Ogbeni Rauf Aregbesola, who is the Chairman of the committee presided over the meeting. He said the President, Major General Muhammadu Buhari (retd.), was committed to the safety and security of all Nigerians irrespective of where they lived. He said the committeeâ€™s priority was to ensure the speedy harmonisation of single database of citizens in the country. Copyright PUNCH.
